The paper discusses a machine learning algorithm for topic modeling, which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP) and information retrieval (IR). The algorithm is designed to handle big data and big models, which suggests that it may fall under the category of large-scale machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of stochastic approximation, which is a common technique in optimization and statistical inference, suggesting that it may also fall under the category of optimization (cs.DS) or artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper discusses the use of probabilistic models and inference, which are common in computational linguistics and NLP, suggesting that it may also fall under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL).
